r bounds show that the sample\ncomplexity need not vary uniformly with the desired error parameter $\\epsilon$:\nfor some values of $\\epsilon$, perturbations in its value have no asymptotic\neffect on the sample complexity, while for other values, any decrease in its\nvalue results in an asymptotically larger sample complexity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 2 Aug 2022 01:44:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-03"}
