i$_{CRS}\\sim 10^{-3}$ and an upper limit of $\\sim 5\\times\n10^{-3}$. Unfortunately, this limit is not sufficient to test global\nacceleration models of CR nuclei, for which values at the level of $\\sim\n10^{-4}$ are required. Such levels could be attained with F/Si data of a few\npercent accuracy at a few tens of TV, possibly within reach of the next\ngeneration of CR experiments.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 2 Aug 2022 09:56:28 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-03"}
