eory prediction in an nDGP model, which is larger than the\n$\\Lambda$CDM prediction at the $3 \\sigma$ level. In $f(R)$ theory we cannot\nnaively compare the results of the fit with the linear theory prediction as\nthis is scale-dependent, but we obtain results that are consistent with the\n$\\Lambda$CDM prediction.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 2 Aug 2022 10:16:12 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 21 Nov 2022 11:28:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-28"}
