Yang's theory of phase transitions and exhibit a\nhyper-dimensional diagram of distinct dynamical regimes. Our findings lead us\nto conclude that the conventional classification of dynamical universality\nclasses based on the algebraic dynamical exponents and asymptotic scaling\nfunctions that characterize hydrodynamic relaxation of the dynamical structure\nfactor is incomplete and calls for refinement.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 2 Aug 2022 13:59:18 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 21 Feb 2023 18:25:16 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 24 Feb 2023 11:47:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-27"}
